tests.title: integration test between client and server
tests.fullTitle: Client integration test between client and server
tests.code:
const
Debug   = require('@superhero/debug'),
log     = new Debug({ debug:false }),
Server  = require('./server'),
server  = Server.from(log),
Client  = require('./client'),
client  = Client.from(log),
port    = 18200,
event   = 'foobar',
body    = { foo:'bar' }
server.listen(port)
client.connect(port)
client.emit(event, body)
server.on(event, (context, data) =>
{
  expect(data).to.deep.equal(body)
  client.client.end()
  server.server.close()
  done()
})

tests.title: possible to remove a listener
tests.fullTitle: Client possible to remove a listener
tests.code:
const
Debug     = require('@superhero/debug'),
log       = new Debug({ debug:false }),
Client    = require('./client'),
client    = Client.from(log),
event     = 'foobar',
listener  = () => {}
expect(client.connectionObserver.dispatcher.events.listenerCount(event)).to.deep.equal(0)
client.on(event, listener)
expect(client.connectionObserver.dispatcher.events.listenerCount(event)).to.deep.equal(1)
client.removeListener(event, listener)
expect(client.connectionObserver.dispatcher.events.listenerCount(event)).to.deep.equal(0)

tests.title: log socket events
tests.code:
const
Debug               = require('@superhero/debug'),
log                 = new Debug({ debug:false }),
ConnectionObserver  = require('./connection-observer'),
connectionObserver  = ConnectionObserver.from(log),
NetSocket           = require('net').Socket,
netSocket           = new NetSocket,
emitter             = connectionObserver.emitter
for(const event of ['close','connection','drain','lookup','timeout','error'])
  expect(event + netSocket.listenerCount(event)).to.be.equal(event + 0)
connectionObserver.logSocketEvents(netSocket, log)
for(const event of ['close','connection','drain','lookup','timeout','error'])
  expect(event + netSocket.listenerCount(event)).to.be.equal(event + 1)

tests.title: handle error
tests.code:
const
Debug                   = require('@superhero/debug'),

Dispatcher              = require('./dispatcher'),
dispatcher              = Dispatcher.from(log),
IncompleteMessageError  = require('./payload-stack/error/incomplete-message'),

tests.title: loop through context buffer to dispatch each message one by one
tests.fullTitle: Dispatcher loop through context buffer to dispatch each message one by one
tests.code:
const
Debug       = require('@superhero/debug'),
log         = new Debug({ debug:false }),
Dispatcher  = require('./dispatcher'),
dispatcher  = Dispatcher.from(log),
Payload     = require('./payload-stack/payload'),
event       = 'foobar',
body        = { foo:'bar' },
buffer      = Payload.from(event, body).toBuffer(),
Emitter     = require('./emitter'),
emitter     = Emitter.from(log),
port        = 18200,
netClient   = require('net').createConnection({ port }),
netServer   = require('net').createServer().listen(port),
Context     = require('./context'),
context     = Context.from(netClient, emitter)
context.payloadStack.push(buffer, buffer)
netClient.on('connect', () => dispatcher.loopThroughContextBufferToDispatchEachMessageOneByOne(context))
let i = 0
dispatcher.events.on(event, (context, data) =>
{
  if(++i === 2)
  {
    expect(data).to.deep.equal(body)
    netClient.end()
    netServer.close()
    done()
  }
})

tests.title: write buffer to socket
tests.code:
const
Debug     = require('@superhero/debug'),
log       = new Debug({ debug:false }),
Emitter   = require('./emitter'),
emitter   = Emitter.from(log),
port      = 18200,
netClient = require('net').createConnection({ port }),
netServer = require('net').createServer().listen(port),
buffer    = Buffer.from('foobar')
netClient.on('connect', async () =>
{
  await emitter.writeBufferToSocket(netClient, buffer)
})
netServer.on('connection', (socket) =>
{
  socket.on('data', (data) =>
  {
    expect(data.toString()).to.be.equal(buffer.toString())
    socket.end()
    netServer.close()
  })
})
netServer.on('close', () => done())

tests.title: emit event with data
tests.code:
const
PayloadStack  = require('./payload-stack'),
payloadStack  = PayloadStack.from(),
Debug         = require('@superhero/debug'),
log           = new Debug({ debug:false }),
Emitter       = require('./emitter'),
emitter       = Emitter.from(log),
port          = 18200,
netClient     = require('net').createConnection({ port }),
netServer     = require('net').createServer().listen(port),
event         = 'foobar',
body          = { foo:'bar' }
netClient.on('connect', async () =>
{
  await emitter.emit(netClient, event, body)
})
netServer.on('connection', (socket) =>
{
  socket.on('data', (data) =>
  {
    payloadStack.push(data)
    const dto = payloadStack.shift()
    expect(dto.event).to.be.equal(event)
    expect(dto.data).to.deep.equal(body)
    socket.end()
    netServer.close()
  })
})
netServer.on('close', () => done())

tests.title: push and shift message from buffer stack
tests.fullTitle: PayloadStack push and shift message from buffer stack
tests.code:
const
PayloadStack  = require('./index'),
payloadStack  = PayloadStack.from(),
foo           = 'foobar',
data          = { foo:'bar' },
Payload       = require('./payload'),
payload       = Payload.from(foo, data),
buffer        = payload.toBuffer()
payloadStack.push(buffer)
const message = payloadStack.shift()
expect(message.event).to.be.equal(foo)
expect(message.data).deep.equal(data)
expect(payloadStack.stack.length).to.be.equal(0)

tests.title: shift a message from the buffer stack that holds a broken message
tests.fullTitle: PayloadStack shift a message from the buffer stack that holds a broken message
tests.code:
const
PayloadStack  = require('./index'),
payloadStack  = PayloadStack.from(),
event         = 'foobar',
data          = { foo:'bar' },
Payload       = require('./payload'),
payload       = Payload.from(event, data),
buffer        = payload.toBuffer().slice(20),
callback      = payloadStack.shift.bind(payloadStack)
payloadStack.push(buffer)
expect(callback).to.throw(Error).with.property('code', 'ERR_INCOMPLETE_MESSAGE')

tests.title: buffer has a header that describes the correct length of the buffer
tests.fullTitle: Payload buffer has a header that describes the correct length of the buffer
tests.code:
const
event   = 'foobar',
data    = { foo:'bar' },
Payload = require('./index'),
payload = Payload.from(event, data),
buffer  = payload.toBuffer(),
length  = buffer.readInt32BE(0)
expect(Payload.HEADER_SIZE + length).to.be.equal(buffer.length)
